context: The patient was brought into the operating room suite, anesthesia administered via endotracheal tube
Following this the patient was draped in standard fashion.
The palate and tonsils were inspected, the palate was suspended with a red rubber catheter passed through the right nostril.
The adenoid pad was removed without difficulty.
Following this, the nasopharynx was unpacked, several discrete bleeding sites were gently coagulated with electrocautery and the nasopharynx and oral cavity were irrigated.
